npm init > initializing a node project and -y means yes
Where this npm init results in creating a folder called 'package.json'.
this package.json store information of this project like project name, version, script, ....

   
npm install express mongoose cors > this command install packages.
it downloads and adds these 3 packages to our node.js project
these libraries like express.js, mongoose, cors are downloaded from npm
we can check in package.json > dependencies 
express - helps build servers & APIs
mongoose - helps node.js connect to mongodb and manage data
cors - allows different websites/apps(frontend) to communiacte to backend

Finally, "npm install express mongoose cors" download these libraries from npm and 
adds them to our node.js project so we build servers, connect to mongodb, and allow 
frontend apps to access backend.


npm install nodemon --save-dev > installs nodemon 
nodemon is development tool that automatically restarts our node.js server when files are changed 
are saved during development phase.






